
/*
 * 1. The [get-value] slot retrieves the value of a node specified by an expression. In this case, the expression `:x:@.arguments/*/limit` points to a [limit] node that is a child of any node under [arguments].
 * 2. The [@.arguments] part locates the [arguments] node in the current context, while the `*/limit` part finds all [limit] nodes under any direct child of [arguments].
 * 3. The result is the value stored in the first [limit] node found under any child node of [arguments].
 * 
 * Use cases:
 * - Extracting a "limit" parameter from HTTP request arguments in an API endpoint.
 * - Reading user-supplied paging or result limit values for database queries.
 * - Validating or processing optional arguments where "limit" may be nested under different parent nodes within [arguments].
 * - Dynamically adapting logic based on the provided "limit" value in multi-argument scenarios.
 */
get-value:x:@.arguments/*/limit
